sequenceDiagram
    %% End-to-end planner sequences:
    %%   1. Console enqueue + Worker submission tick - happy path
    %%   2. Provision-expiry sweeper - submitted -> superseded; new attempt inserted
    %%
    %% Visibility boundary (matches the package layout):
    %%   plannerapi/ : the only thing Console BFF imports. The Planner
    %%                 participant below sits inside this box.
    %%   internal/   : compiler-blocked from outside the planner module.
    %%                 TaskStore, Worker, and BatchClient all live here;
    %%                 BFF never references them by type.
    %%
    %% Cancellation is NOT a planner-driven flow: the OpenAI Batches API
    %% exposes /cancel on MDS, and any user-facing cancel travels through
    %% MDS directly. The planner observes the resulting MDS terminal state
    %% on its read-time overlay (Planner.GetJob / ListJobs) and surfaces
    %% it via JobView.LifecycleState - see the README "JobLifecycleState"
    %% derivation table.

    box rgb(227,242,253) Console (external to planner)
        participant UI as Console UI
        participant BFF as Console BFF
    end
    box rgb(255,248,225) plannerapi (Console-facing public)
        participant P as Planner
    end
    box rgb(255,243,224) internal (compiler-blocked from outside)
        participant TS as TaskStore
        participant W as Worker
        participant BC as BatchClient
    end
    box rgb(252,228,236) External services
        participant RM as Resource Manager
        participant MDS
    end

    Note over UI,MDS: 1. Enqueue and Worker submission

    UI->>BFF: CreateJob
    BFF->>P: Enqueue EnqueueRequest<br/>JobID, Accelerator, ModelTemplate, Profile, BatchPayload
    Note over P: planner expands Accelerator + ModelTemplate<br/>into the resolved rmtypes.ResourceProvisionSpec<br/>(Groups, Credential, TimeWindow) and stamps it<br/>onto the PlannerTask before persisting
    P->>TS: TaskQueue.Enqueue PlannerTask Attempt=1 state queued
    TS-->>P: ok
    P-->>BFF: EnqueueResult queued
    BFF-->>UI: JobID status queued

    Note over W: dispatcher tick - single process<br/>one dispatcher + N task goroutines

    W->>TS: TaskQueue.Dequeue (TaskIDs=nil) for FCFS<br/>or Peek + SchedulerFunc + Dequeue (TaskIDs=...) for custom policy
    TS-->>W: claimed PlannerTasks - state claimed

    W->>RM: acquire capacity for TaskID + PlannerTask.ProvisionSpec
    alt insufficient resources
        RM-->>W: error wrapped as ErrInsufficientResources
        W->>TS: TaskLifecycle.Nack with backoff
    else success
        RM-->>W: RM-side response<br/>worker translates into mds.Provision<br/>ID, Allocations, ExpiresAt
        Note over W: idempotent per TaskID<br/>a re-claiming worker after crash gets the same handle back
    end

    Note over W: Worker.submit private method<br/>build mds.MDSBatchSubmission from PlannerTask + Provision
    W->>BC: BatchClient.GetBatch by aibrix.job_id - pre-submit dedup
    alt batch already exists
        BC-->>W: existing BatchView
        Note over W: short-circuit - Ack with existing BatchID
    else not found
        BC-->>W: not found
        W->>BC: BatchClient.CreateBatch with MDSBatchSubmission
        BC->>MDS: POST v1 batches with extra_body.aibrix
        MDS-->>BC: Batch
        BC-->>W: BatchView with BatchID
    end

    W->>TS: TaskLifecycle.Ack TaskID BatchID ProvisionID ProvisionExpiresAt
    Note over W,RM: Provision NOT released here<br/>held past submit so the sweeper can detect<br/>provision expired before MDS finished<br/>release happens on Fail, post-MaxAttempts Nack,<br/>or observed MDS-terminal

    Note over P,MDS: 2. Provision-expiry sweep - planner-internal background

    Note over RM,MDS: RM-side expiry tears down GPU pods<br/>MDS marks its batch failed or expired on its own<br/>planner does NOT release capacity here

    loop every sweep tick
        P->>TS: TaskLifecycle.ListExpiringProvisions before, limit
        TS-->>P: candidate PlannerTasks - each is one attempt

        loop for each candidate
            P->>TS: TaskLifecycle.Supersede supersededTaskID newTask
            Note over TS: atomic - prior task to superseded, BatchID kept for audit<br/>new task inserted - Attempt+1, state queued, fresh TaskID<br/>fresh TaskID forces a fresh RM-side capacity allocation
            TS-->>P: ok
        end
    end
